The paper focuses on the analysis of deleted questions on Stack Overflow, which is a community-based question answering website for programmers. The study involves the characterization of deleted questions over a period of five years and the prediction of question deletion at the time of creation. The paper uses various features related to user profile, community-generated content, question content, and syntactic style to build a predictive model. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Software Engineering (cs.SE), Cybersecurity (cs.CY), and Computation and Language (cs.CL).
